Qt Hldplugin version 3.1.1 is a bugfix release.

The most important changes are listed in this document. For a complete
list of changes, see the Git log for the Qt Hldplugin sources that
you can check out from the public Git repository. For example:

git clone git://gitorious.org/qt-hldplugin/qt-hldplugin.git
git log --cherry-pick --pretty=oneline v3.1.0..v3.1.1

General
   * Fixed editing of MIME types while filtering is applied
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12149)

Managing and Building Projects
   * Fixed performance regression in Issues pane (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12109)

Qbs Projects
   * Fixed support for VS2013 compiler (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11025)

C++ Support
   * Fixed issue with missing semantic highlighting (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11367)

Qt Quick Designer
   * Fixed several UI issues (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12040, QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12035,
     QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11904, QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12018)
   * Fixed anchor and alignment handling (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12006)

Diff Viewer
   * Fixed crash when showing binary file containing carriage return character
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12056)

Version Control Systems
   * Git
      * Fixed encoding issues on Window
      * Fixed crash when closing Qt Hldplugin after revert (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12099)

FakeVim

Platform Specific

QNX
   * Fixed crash when no device is configured (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12143)
   * Fixed Qt environment settings for running on devices (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12171)

Android
   * Fixed selection of Ant executable on OS X (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12184)

iOS
   * Fixed parsing of build issues
   * Added warning if provisioning profile does not contain selected device
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-12175)

